quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  109,1,"Say: “O unbelievers!”"
  109,2,I do not worship those that you worship
  109,3,neither do you worship Him Whom I worship
  109,4,nor will I worship those whom you have worshipped
  109,5,nor are you going to worship Him Whom I worship
  109,6,"To you is your religion, and to me, my religion"
  110,1,"When the help comes from Allah, and victory (is granted)"
  110,2,and you see people entering Allah's religion in multitudes
  110,3,then extol the praise of your Lord and pray to Him for forgiveness. For He indeed is ever disposed to accept repentance
  111,1,"Destroyed were the hands of Abu Lahab, and he lay utterly doomed"
  111,2,"His wealth did not avail him, nor his acquisitions"
  111,3,"Surely, he will be cast into a Flaming Fire"
  111,4,"along with his wife, that carrier of slanderous tales"
  111,5,upon her neck shall be a rope of palm-fibre